'''Jharkhand State Electricity Board''' is a [[Government of Jharkhand]] enterprise, entrusted with the generation and distribution of electrical power in the state of [[Jharkhand]], India. It suffers a loss of more than {{INR}}1,000 crore (USD 200mn) every year.<ref name=hindu/>
In 2011, it was revealed that in the last ten years, as much as {{INR}}80 crores in outstanding dues to various units had been waived.<ref name=hindu>http://www.thehindu.com/news/states/other-states/article2062878.ece</ref> For example, ex-Chief Minister [[Madhu Koda]], in prison for graft since 2008, waived of a {{INR}}10 crore bill from a company owned by fellow minister [[Vinod Sinha]], who is also in jail on graft charges.
==Power Plants== * [[Patratu Thermal Power Station]]. It an installed capacity of 840&nbsp;MW. The generating units of the power plant are very old and is operating at around 10% PLF.<ref>http://articles.economictimes.indiatimes.com/2010-12-29/news/27607079_1_ntpc-official-ptps-patratu-thermal-power-station</ref> The power plant is undergoing renovation.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.jseb.org.in/ptps.html |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2014-08-21 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140821222227/http://www.jseb.org.in/ptps.html |archivedate=2014-08-21 |df= }}</ref> * Subernrekha Hydel Power Station, Sikidiri, a 130 MW (2x65 MW) hydel power plant.<ref>http://www.jseb.org.in/shrp.html</ref>
