{{Infobox power station | name = Rothenburg Solar Park | name_official = | image = | image_size = | image_caption = | image_alt = | location_map = Germany | location_map_size = | location_map_caption = | coordinates = <!-- {{coord| | |region:DE_type:landmark|display=inline,title}} --> | country = Germany | location = [[Rothenburg, Oberlausitz]] | status = O | construction_began = | commissioned = December 2009 | decommissioned = | cost = | owner = | operator = | solar_type = PV | ps_units_operational = 273,240 [[First Solar]] | solar_csp_heliostats = | solar_site_area = {{convert|70|ha|acre|0|abbr=on}} | ps_electrical_capacity = 20.5 [[Megawatt|MW]]<sub>p</sub> | ps_electrical_cap_fac = | website = | extra = }}
The '''Rothenburg Solar Park''' is a [[photovoltaic power station]] in [[Rothenburg, Oberlausitz]] in Germany. It has a capacity of 20.5 [[megawatt]]s (MW). The solar park is equipped with 273,240&nbsp; [[Cadmium telluride photovoltaics|CdTe]]-[[Thin film solar cell|modules]] from [[First Solar]], and 11&nbsp;[[Siemens]] [[PV system#Solar inverters|central inverters]]. The project was commissioned in 2009.<ref>[http://www.exenewable.com/projectProfile.asp?id=20722 eXenewable Project Profile Page - Rothenburg, PV, Germany]</ref>
